parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of rear brakes can lead to sudden loss of braking power, causing accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Rear brakes need to be replaced frequently (every 4000 miles)
rear brakes feel like they're always on
crunching sound when applying rear brakes
metal-to-metal sound when brakes are worn out
rear wheel locks up or skids.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch slipping can cause loss of power, stalling, or difficulty shifting gears, leading to accidents or unsafe situations, especially when merging into traffic.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission jumping out of 4th gear and into a false neutral between 4th and 5th gear can cause a loss of power and control, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when passing other vehicles.
symptoms: The transmission jumps out of 4th gear under strong acceleration
the transmission shifts into neutral instead of 5th gear
the vehicle loses power
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting into 5th gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Seizure Due to Ball Bearing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball bearings can cause the engine to seize, resulting in sudden loss of power, stalling, or even engine failure, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine seizes or locks up
the vehicle stalls or loses power
unusual noises or grinding sounds from the engine
the engine overheats
the vehicle is unable to move.
